title: The Rabindranath Tagore Collection - Rabindranath Tagore
description:
Waxkeep Publishing Collections provide history's greatest authors' collected works in a convenient collection complete with a linked table of contents. Our goal is to provide the most complete, and most easy to read collections in the marketplace.

Rabindranath Tagore, a native of Bengal, was the first non-European to win the Nobel Prize in Literature (1913). The Rabindranath Tagore Collection includes Gitanjali and 49 other stores, plays, and poems.

Included are the following:
